modules.description: This module provides functions to interact with an InfluxDB server, specifically for pinging the server and writing a list of data points to a specified database. It works with InfluxDB's native data structures, such as `Influxdb.Point.t` for time-series data and `Influxdb.Protocol.ping_response` for handling ping responses. Concrete use cases include sending metrics or logs to InfluxDB for storage and monitoring server availability.

This module enables interaction with an InfluxDB server by providing functions to send time-series data points and check server availability via ping. It operates on InfluxDB-specific data types such as `Point.t` for data points and `ping_response` for health checks. Use cases include logging application metrics and verifying database connectivity in real-time monitoring systems.
